               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 4 works (a-d)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous works on Sufism. Volume not dated; individual items are dated, ranging from 7 Ramaz̤ān 1107-4 Z̲ī Qaʿdah 1108/31 March 1696-25 May 1697. Dense shikastah āmīz throughout by the same hand; scribe not identified. Loose paper wrapper (text on EIC government of India legislation referring to date 1820), watermarked (initials VEIC; undated); torn and stained. Lacks binding. Stamped foliation. Folios detached and unbound; stained, cropped, torn, desiccating, excessive wormhole damage, later repairs detaching. Condition extremely fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1156-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="31v">ff. 1v-31v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. 
</p>
                        <p>Unidentified Ṣūfī treatise by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work consists of several fātiḥah with multiple subsections. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 31v): completed by an unnamed devotee of the Ṣūfī saint, Shāh ʿInāyat Allāh Ḥāfiẓ, Tuesday, 7 Ramaz̤ān in RY 40 [Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I] (1107)/31 March 1696. 
</p>
                        <p>Dense shikastah āmīz, with rubrics and overlining in red. 
</p>
                        <p>Dense annotations and corrections in margins throughout; cropped and damaged by later repairs. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian, Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1156-item2">
                     <locus from="32v" to="51r">ff. 32v-51r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7408">Muḥammad Yūsuf ibn Muḥammad Ṭāhir </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7408">محمّد يوسف ابن محمّد طاهر</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21671">Lubb al-daqāʾiq va khalaṣṣ al-ḥaqāʾiq</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21671">لبّ الدّقائق و خلصّ الحقائق</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī malfūẓ or authorised biography with collected sayings of (?) Shaykh [Abū al-Barakāt] ʿĪsá Jund Allāh Shaṭṭārī Qādirī (d. 1622), the student of Shaykh Burhān al-Dīn [ibn Kabīr Muḥammad ibn ʿAlī Burhānpūrī Gujarātī] al-Ṣiddīqī al-Ḥusaynī al-Shaṭṭārī, called Rāz-ii Ilāhī (d. 1083/1672), by Muḥammad Yūsuf ibn Muḥammad Ṭāhir. 
</p>
                        <p>The conclusion to the work is followed by a short statement by the author stating the work was well received by its subject and circulated only after permission or iz̲n was granted. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 51r): completed by an unnamed devotee of the Ṣūfī saint, Shāh ʿInāyat Allāh Qādirī, 4 Z̲ī Qaʿdah 1108/25 May 1697. 
</p>
                        <p>Same dense shikastah āmīz hand as item a. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1156-item3">
                     <locus from="51v" to="57r">ff. 51v-57r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Brief selection from the collected correspondence on Ṣūfī themes of ʿAbd al-Jalīl Jawnpūrī, a contemporary of Shaykh Aḥmad Sihrindī, by an unnamed editor. 
</p>
                        <p>The collection consists of indications for thirty-nine letters in total. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 57r): completed by an unnamed devotee of the Ṣūfī saint, Shāh ʿInāyat Allāh Qādirī, Tuesday, 11 Z̲ī Qaʿdah 1107/12 June 1696. 
</p>
                        <p>Same dense shikastah āmīz hand as item a. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21672">Maktūbāt-i ʿAbd al-Jalīl</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21672">مكتوبات عبد الجليل</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1156-item4">
                     <locus from="57v" to="85r">ff. 57v-85r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Rare account of the Ṣūfī discourses and biography of Burhān al-Dīn ibn Kabīr Muḥammad ibn ʿAlī Burhānpūrī Gujarātī, called Rāz-ii Ilāhī (d. 1083/1672), compiled by his follower, the historian, governor of Akbarābād (Agra), and author of the <title>Naghmāt-i ʿishq</title>, ʿAlī ʿAskarī ibn Muḥammad Taqī ibn Muḥammad Qāsim al-Khvāfī, later entitled ʿĀqil Khān with the takhalluṣ "Rāzī" after his master (d. 1108/1697), and completed in 1053/1643-4 according to the chronogrammatic title. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work contains important information on the author’s initiation and that of Prince Awrangzīb, later Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I. 
This is a significantly early copy of the work, datable to within the author’s lifetime. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 85r): completed by an unnamed devotee of the Ṣūfī saint, Shāh ʿInāyat Allāh Ḥāfiẓ, 9 Z̲ī al-Ḥijjah in RY 40 of Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I (1107)/10 July 1696. 
</p>
                        <p>Same dense shikastah āmīz hand as item a. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21673">S̲amarāt al-ḥayāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21673">ثمراة الحياة</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658530.0x000001 viaf_56260243" type="supplied" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">ʿĀqil Khān-i Rāzī, -1696</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_56260243">عاقل خان رازی</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
